text: Altes Amt Lemförde is a Samtgemeinde ("collective municipality") in the district of Diepholz, in Lower Saxony, Germany. Its seat is in the village Lemförde. The Samtgemeinde Altes Amt Lemförde consists of the following municipalities: * Brockum * Hüde * Lembruch * Lemförde * Marl * Quernheim * Stemshorn ==References== Category:Samtgemeinden in Lower Saxony
title: Altes Amt Lemförde
